BASIC UBANTU LINUX COMMANDS
------------------------

pwd – Print current working directory

cd – Change directory

ls – List directory contents

mkdir – Make a new directory

rmdir – Remove empty directory

touch – Create a new empty file

rm – Remove files or directories

cp – Copy files or directories

mv – Move or rename files/directories

cat – View file content

nano – Edit files in terminal using nano editor

vi – Edit files using vi editor

clear – Clear the terminal screen

exit – Close the terminal session

sudo – Run command with root privileges

apt update – Update package list

apt upgrade – Upgrade installed packages

history – Show previously used commands

man – Show manual for a command

echo – Display a message or variable

ls Command Options:

ls – List files in current directory

ls -l – Long listing format (permissions, size, etc.)

ls -a – Show all files including hidden ones

ls -la – Long format + all files (hidden too)

ls -lh – Human-readable sizes in long format

ls -R – List directories and subdirectories recursively

ls -t – Sort by modification time (latest first)

ls -S – Sort by file size (largest first)

ls -r – Reverse order while sorting

ls -d */ – Show only directories

ls --color – Colorize the output

ls -1 – One file per line

ls -i – Show inode number

ls -X – Sort alphabetically by extension

ls -F – Add indicator (/ for dir, * for exec)
